<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><table-reference graph="None" id="_b244e0e1-8c8a-47e2-9878-b63b06f10b7e"><num>6.2.1a</num><title id="_c67ce486-4ec4-4dd7-b586-f6b696df28a8">Subfloor openings</title><table id="_391a5980-e3c3-413e-b010-dc31f0ec5e3b" keycol="1"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="001" colnum="1" colwidth="144.00*"/><colspec colname="002" colnum="2" colwidth="144.00*"/><colspec colname="003" colnum="3" colwidth="144.00*"/><thead><row><entry>Climatic zone (see Figure 6.2.1a)</entry><entry>Minimum aggregate subfloor ventilation openings with no <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_b8fa0d3c-4349-4f67-bda2-7d61b98763d6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref> (mm<b id="_d92193e5-d63c-48c2-8877-544f473256c3"><sup id="_b86cb534-d14a-414a-85cc-31dc0d725852">2</sup></b>/m of wall)</entry><entry>Minimum aggregate subfloor ventilation openings with ground sealed with impervious <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_9a71cca4-ea2c-4760-8266-65ccfa823ecd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref> (mm<b id="_e8cdaed4-8c5c-4afc-9381-04d88a2e7a1a"><sup id="_c068e87b-86ce-44c0-b21c-945f851d1590">2</sup></b>/m of wall)</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry>A</entry><entry>2000</entry><entry>1000</entry></row><row><entry>B</entry><entry>4000</entry><entry>2000</entry></row><row><entry>C</entry><entry>6000</entry><entry>3000</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><desc-note id="_4507ceef-624e-4b0a-9d40-bffef48894fe"><p>In situations where openings in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_c88600b5-d795-47ad-a66b-eaa9998b3c70" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external walls</xref> and internal subfloor walls, including <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1455_0.7.0.xml#_c162af82-2477-499d-bdb1-39be88ffa668" id="_d2290c1b-1a9a-44d2-933a-e4f5890f556a" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">separating walls</xref>, are not able to be provided, additional measures must be provided to ensure that the overall level of ventilation of the subfloor space is maintained. This may include measures similar to those in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1543_1.5.0.xml#_aee908b0-17e5-42a6-914b-b93120ad20eb" id="_d31ed0b2-b4a0-4399-8650-2f263ef54ab2" scope="local" type="subclause">6.2.1(5)</xref> i.e. providing durability class timbers, or having the ground sealed in the subfloor space with an impervious <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_e8f3b721-6051-41a9-94cc-95958fd91198" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">membrane</xref>.</p></desc-note></table-reference>